```python
import torch.nn as nn

class TwoHiddenLayerNN(nn.Module):
    def __init__(self, input_dim, hidden_dim_range=(32, 128), output_dim=1):
        super(TwoHiddenLayerNN, self).__init__()
        # Input to first hidden layer
        self.hidden1 = nn.Linear(input_dim, hidden_dim_range[0])
        # First hidden layer with ReLU activation
        self.relu1 = nn.ReLU()
        # Second hidden layer
        self.hidden2 = nn.Linear(hidden_dim_range[0], hidden_dim_range[1])
        # Second hidden layer with ReLU activation
        self.relu2 = nn.ReLU()
        # Output layer
        self.output = nn.Linear(hidden_dim_range[1], output_dim)
    
    def forward(self, x):
        # Forward pass through the network
        x = self.hidden1(x)
        x = self.relu1(x)
        x = self.hidden2(x)
        x = self.relu2(x)
        x = self.output(x)
        return x
```
